# Lab5Hurtak Space Game

## Abstract

This project is a Java Swing space game created for the Solo Lab 5 Assignment. The player controls a spaceship, fires projectiles, avoids obstacles, collects health power-ups, collects purple orb power-ups, uses a rechargeable shield, and tries to survive until the countdown timer reaches zero.

The game includes multiple levels, moving stars, sound effects, health management, shield mechanics, extra-shot upgrades, and a scoring system.

## Features

- Random colored moving stars in the background
- Spaceship player image
- Blue score text
- 4 x 1 obstacle sprite sheet
- Fire and collision WAV sound effects
- Shield activated with the Control key
- Shield recharge bar
- Player health display
- Random health power-ups
- Random purple orb power-ups
- Up to 5 extra shots from purple orbs
- Countdown timer
- Three difficulty levels
- Win and lose conditions

## Game Rules

- The player starts with 3 health.
- The player wins by surviving for 90 seconds.
- The player loses when health reaches 0.
- Health power-ups restore health.
- Purple orbs provide additional projectiles.
- The shield protects the player from obstacle collisions.
- Level 3 becomes significantly more difficult.

## Controls

- Left Arrow = Move Left
- Right Arrow = Move Right
- Space Bar = Fire Projectiles
- Control Key = Activate Shield
- Escape Key = Reset Game

## Assets Used

The following files are stored in:

src/main/resources/assets

- ship.png
- obstacles.png
- health.png
- fire.wav
- collision.wav

## Technologies Used

- Java
- Java Swing
- Graphics2D
- AudioSystem
- BufferedImage
- Timer
- ArrayList Collections

## Author

Alexander Matthew Hurtak

## Course

IST 242 – Java Programming

## How To Run

1. Open the project in IntelliJ IDEA.
2. Verify JDK 17 or newer is installed.
3. Build the project.
4. Run the SpaceGame class.
5. Use the keyboard controls to play.

